issue.body:
Sorry for not following the issue template.

Prettier user raised an issue https://github.com/prettier/prettier/discussions/17249, after investigation, I found this bug is caused by turbopack, but I can't really say that's their fault, it's an edge case.

Looking at https://unpkg.com/browse/@babel/parser@7.26.10/lib/index.js L3195 and L3205

We have this code

```js
    if (next === 109) {
      // ...
      var isDecimal = true;
    }

    // ...

    if (isDecimal) {
      // ...
    }
```

and turbopack bundled it as

```js
   if (next === 109) {
     // ...
     var isDecimal = true;
   }

   // ...

   if ("TURBOPACK compile-time truthy", 1) {
      // ...
   }

   "TURBOPACK unreachable";
   // ...
```

Then `if (isDecimal)` branch becomes `true`.

I think we should define a local variable instead of using `var`?

Code in source https://github.com/babel/babel/blob/33110bf6a6e47ee084a79050a20ea67d9317af20/packages/babel-parser/src/tokenizer/index.ts#L1290

cc @liuxingbaoyu

body:
Reduced to a minimal reproduction:

```js
const shouldRun = () => false;

export default function Home() {
  if (shouldRun()) {
    var x = true;
  }
  if (x) {
    console.log("should not run");
  }
  return <h1>Home</h1>;
}
```

